Transactions are logged and digital signatures captured for use in autogenerating documentation, such as form 0751. This lesson covers community and role responsibilities in the Asset Turn In process. For more information about the process, please go to Appendix A - Turn In Asset Business Process to view the flowchart and process narrative. ## User Roles and Responsibilities The audience for this training includes the following user roles: | Role | Responsibility | |------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Evaluation of the work order by the appropriate Supervisory level is required to determine the need for pre-turn in work (e.g., decontamination, uninstallation, data sanitization, Freon removal). These Evaluation Work Orders appear in the Inbox/Assignments portlet of FM Admin, FM Work Order Clerk, and HTM Admin based on the Responsible Department of the Asset. NOTE: Any work order with a Responsible Department of MULTI will appear in the Inbox/Assignments portlet of both FM and HTM. IMPORTANT! Should a Turn In Work Order contain an Asset(s) with open wor

NOTE: Any work order with a Responsible Department of MULTI will appear in the Inbox/Assignments portlet of both FM and HTM. IMPORTANT! Should a Turn In Work Order contain an Asset(s) with open work orders other than the Turn In Work Order, the following message will display. The Asset(s) affected will be listed. Though not required, it is recommended to CLOSE open work orders, other than the Turn In Work Order, if appropriate. An open work order is a work order in any status other than CLOSE. This is also a good time to verify the Asset(s) do not have ACTIVE PMs. If so, they should be changed to INACTIVE. Figure 1.
